{
  "texts": [
    "When there is an anomaly in the input image, this is referred to as a positive (P).",
    "A TP is proclaimed when a classifier accurately segments and classifies an image as a pothole road abnormality (PRA).",
    "If such a PRA is discovered to be a smooth road (SR), a false negative (FN) is declared.",
    "Similarly, if the input image is an SR, it is referred to as a negative image (N).",
    "When a classifier correctly recognises an SR image as an SR, a true negative (TN) is declared; conversely, a false positive (FP) is declared if an SR is correctly classified as a PRA."
  ]
}